00:00:31.461 --> 00:00:35.361
There's a lot of attempts to make dedicated spots for bikes

00:00:35.944 --> 00:00:38.024
Like dedicated biking lanes or

00:00:38.520 --> 00:00:41.240
dedicated space on the sidewalk

00:00:41.240 --> 00:00:43.640
but it doesn't really get respected

00:00:43.640 --> 00:00:45.825
You'll have like a bike lane that goes for a street

00:00:45.825 --> 00:00:47.454
and then the next street has nothing

00:00:47.454 --> 00:00:49.674
This street seems to be bike-friendly

00:00:49.674 --> 00:00:53.345
and then the next street over there has nothing marked off for bicycles

00:00:53.345 --> 00:00:55.807
The continuity doesn't really add up here

00:00:59.463 --> 00:01:01.143
So what ends up happening

00:01:01.143 --> 00:01:04.535
is you basically just share the road with the drivers

00:01:04.535 --> 00:01:05.764
and it's totally cool

00:01:05.764 --> 00:01:07.022
